[SN]TITLE[SN]
Stephen Carson murder: Man arrested in Belfast

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police investigating the killing of a man who was shot in front of his family at his home four months ago have arrested a man on suspicion of murder.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Stephen Carson, 28, was shot in the head through a bathroom door at Walmer Street, Belfast, on 26 February.
He was having a meal with his partner and nine-year-old son when an armed gang forced their way into the house.
The arrested man, who is 35, was detained in Belfast and remains in police custody.
